Title: Avoid oversized Xcode script input lists

## Problem

When Breeze Icons is generated with the Xcode CMake generator, the custom
command for `breeze-icons.qrc` adds every SVG icon to the Xcode script phase's
`inputPaths`.

Breeze contains enough SVG files for this generated list to exceed macOS's
process argument and environment size limit. Xcode then fails before executing
the resource-generation command:

    unable to spawn process '/bin/sh' (Argument list too long)

This prevents Breeze Icons from being cross-compiled for iOS.

## Proposed change

Keep the complete per-SVG dependency list for other CMake generators, but omit
it when generating an Xcode project. The Xcode custom command still depends on
the three theme input files and still generates the same QRC and icon content.

## Impact

This changes only incremental dependency tracking under the Xcode generator.
Changing an individual SVG may require explicitly rebuilding or regenerating
the Xcode project. Other generators retain the existing per-file dependency
tracking.

